Ogbonnaya Ikokwu, Umuahia The kidnapped female presenter of the Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeriaâ€™s Pacesetter FM, Umuahia, in Abia State, Chinenye Iwuoha, has regained her freedom. Iwuoha was abducted by gunmen on Monday while she was leaving the Broadcasting House in company with her colleagues. Her abductors later demanded N20m ransom before her release. A source at the radio station, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said Iwuoha was released unhurt. The Commissioner of Police in the state, Janet Agbede, confirmed her release. The CP said the kidnappers released Iwuoha unconditionally as the police mounted serious pressure on them. Copyright PUNCH.
